Package: BCallometryRCFS
Type: Package
Title: Allometric Equations for BC Forestry
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2026-06-22
Authors@R: c(
    person("Derek Felix", "Sattler",
           email = "Derek.Sattler@nrcan-rncan.gc.ca",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Yong", "Luo",
           role = "ctb",
           comment = "Original implementation in FAIBCompiler and FAIBBase, Copyright 2019 Province of British Columbia"))
Description: Provides allometric equations for British Columbia forestry
  workflows. Supports four primary applications: (1) height-diameter (H-D)
  modelling, with prediction functions for six model forms (Naslund, Curtis,
  logistic, Korf, Weibull, Richards) and fixed-effects or mixed-effects
  fitting, to estimate missing tree heights from DBH; (2) individual tree
  volume including gross whole-stem volume (WSV), gross merchantable volume
  (MER), and stump volume, using Kozak's (2002) KBEC variable-exponent taper
  equation (16 BC species, 13 BEC zones) -- all volumes are inside-bark and
  gross (no defect deductions); (3) tree stem profile (inside-bark diameter
  at any height) enabling log-section volume estimates; and (4) aboveground
  tree biomass by component (stem wood, stem bark, branches, foliage) in dry
  kg for 45 Canadian species using Lambert et al. (2005) and Ung et al.
  (2008). Species crosswalk utilities (species_correction(),
  bc_species_to_sp0(), bc_species_to_biomass_name()) translate raw BC
  inventory codes (e.g. 'PLI', 'FDI', 'SW') to the SP0 group codes required
  for volume and the common names required for biomass. Portions of the
  implementation are derived from the FAIBCompiler and FAIBBase R packages,
  Copyright 2019 Province of British Columbia, with original contributions by
  Yong Luo.
